[1] Saudi Arabia, 1 new recovery - MOH 21 Nov 2014
Date: Fri 21 Nov 2014
Source: Saudi Arabia Ministry of Health [edited]
http://www.moh.gov.sa/en/CCC/PressReleases/Pages/Statistics-2014-11-21-001.aspx


As of 12:00 noon on 21 Nov 2014, there have been a total of:
808 laboratory-confirmed cases of MERS-CoV including
346 deaths
451 recovered cases and
11 currently active cases

Information on newly reported recovery:
Jeddah: 49-year-old expat male, non-healthcare worker, no history co-morbidities

--
Communicated by:
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>

[The number of cases of MERS-CoV infection reported by Saudi Arabia is now 808 including 346 deaths (case fatality rate 42.8 percent). The newly reported recovered case is most likely the 49-year-old expat male in Jeddah confirmed as having MERS-CoV infection on 7 Nov 2014, who at the time of report was noted to be in critical condition. At that time a history of possible animal exposure was under investigation.

A map showing the location of this case can be found at the source URL. - Mod.MPP]

******
[2] Saudi Arabia, 1 new case, 1 new death - MOH 20 Nov 2014, RFI
Date: Thu 20 Nov 2014
Source: Saudi Arabia Ministry of Health [edited]
http://www.moh.gov.sa/en/CCC/PressReleases/Pages/Statistics-2014-11-20-001.aspx


Information on newly laboratory-confirmed case:
Alkharj: 48-year-old Saudi female, non-healthcare worker, currently in stable condition, history of pre-existing co-morbidities, no history of animal exposure, no history of contact with suspected or confirmed case in healthcare environment, history of contact with suspected or confirmed case in the community.

Information on newly reported death:
Taif: 79-year-old Saudi female, non-healthcare worker, history of pre-existing co-morbidities

--
Communicated by:
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>

[With today's newly confirmed case in Alkharj it brings the total number of cases reported in Alkharj in the past 10 days (since 11 Nov 2014) to 4, with 3 cases having been reported in the past 3 days. Of the cases reported in Alkharj this month (November 2014), one was under investigation for possible animal as well as healthcare associated contacts, one was under investigation for possible contact with suspected or confirmed cases in both the healthcare environment and the community, one had a definite history of animal exposure, and one had a history of contact with a suspected or confirmed case in the community. It appears as though there may be a chain of transmission ongoing in Alkharj. More information on investigations ongoing in Alkharj would be greatly appreciated.

Today's newly reported death is most likely the 79-year-old female in Taif reported as a confirmed case on 12 Nov 2014 at which time she was noted to be in critical condition. History of possible exposures (animal contact, contact with suspected or confirmed cases in the healthcare environment or community) was under investigation at the time of the report of confirmation.

A map showing the locations of the cases can be found at the source URL. - Mod.MPP]

